y father died in 1911. And - I was married by then of course and I stayed in Corstorphine and worked - and serving my time. See, when my folks went to Carnoustie, I was - taken in by a - apprentice boss into the family you see, to serve the rest of my tim
e which was fully two years, served five years altogether. So - I was there - \lquote 
til I got married, and then I - I still stayed in Corstorphine of course after I was married and - I had - that would be - well 1905 I was married you see. And - I - Nan and Jim, boy and a girl. And I was there \lquote 
