 I played football for a while, two or three years, but that was before I was married. And then after I was married I was Secretary for the club that I - a lady - a Doctor Todd raised after the war, I was Secretary for a - number of years. That was a Mrs 
a
nd a Doctor Todd Cloud. Her father had this mills and - flour mills at Leith. And she - she raised this club you see for lads that came back from the army and - she paid everything and - cost her three or four hundred a year to - we had a gymnastic class 
